50|$|When {{a company}} is being wound up or goes into administration, the liquidator, {{receiver}} or administrator may make a formal declaration that they expect no residual distribution to shareholders (all money being exhausted paying creditors first). Shareholders may then, if they wish, claim a capital loss on the shares as if they disposed of them for <b>nil</b> <b>consideration.</b> If a subsequent liquidation distribution does occur then it is treated as a capital gain.|$|E

